People make a point that others use terms like "autistic" too liberally, but if you look at any older psychiatric textbook it says stuff like "autism is a schizoid dementia of the personality", it was never that serious. Real professionals know to work around all the terminology.

Really most ppl would be surprised if they read a few textbooks, even from the last part of the 20th century, concepts like "dementia", "schizophrenia", "autism" that seem coherent even to people outside the field today are all a lot more intermixed than anyone would assume now.
